        <h2>Employment prospects</h2>
        <h2>1. Network Engineer</h2>
        <p>Mainly responsible for network construction, management, and maintenance of enterprises, organizations, or institutions, ensuring network availability and security, and able to configure equipment and network planning according to specific needs</p>
       <h2>2. network administrator</h2>
       <p>Responsible for monitoring and maintaining network systems, ensuring their normal and stable operation, and resolving network failures and security issues</p>
       <h2>3. Network Security Expert</h2>
       <p>Use various technologies and means to manage and maintain network security, prevent network attacks and data theft, and establish security policies and prevention systems</p> 
       <h2>4. Wireless Network Engineer</h2>
       <p>Mainly responsible for the construction, management, and maintenance of wireless networks for enterprises or organizations, designing and optimizing wireless coverage, ensuring the availability and security of wireless networks</p> 
       <h2>5. Autonomous Traffic Network Controller</h2>
       <p>Responsible for monitoring and managing autonomous transportation network systems, coordinating station and train scheduling.</p> 
        
